==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simpai
<hw>Sim"pai</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[Malay
<ets>simpei</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A long-tailed monkey
(<spn>Semnopitchecus melalophus</spn>) native of Sumatra. It has a crest
of black hair. The forehead and cheeks are fawn color, the upper parts
tawny and red, the under parts white. Called also <altname>black-crested
monkey</altname>, and <altname>sinpae</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simper</ent>⟦br⟧
